<paragraph blockId="91.[264,1323,345,454]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Diagnosis: Dorsocentral bristles in three pairs. Prosternum narrow, bare. Wing pigmented, with two transverse, zigzag, clear bands beyond end of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[945,976,398,415]" fontSize="7" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">2+3</subScript>
; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1012,1042,398,415]" fontSize="7" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">2+3</subScript>
short and straight. Distiphallus with nodes on paired whip­like sclerites.
</paragraph>
